♪ SHE JUST CAN'T MAKE ♪

04:38.669 --> 04:42.760
♪ UP HER MIND

05:10.440 --> 05:12.224
-SUMMER, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE HERE.

05:12.355 --> 05:14.270
-I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE HERE.

05:14.401 --> 05:16.228
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL
ME OR ANYTHING?

05:16.359 --> 05:17.404
-I WANTED TO SURPRISE YOU.

05:17.534 --> 05:19.231
-WELL YOU DID.

05:20.668 --> 05:21.538
-I MISS YOU.

05:23.148 --> 05:25.760
-UM, SO HOW DOES IT FEEL

05:25.890 --> 05:28.719
BEING A BIG INTERNATIONAL
SURFING CHAMPION?

05:29.372 --> 05:31.156
-IT'S GREAT, BUT
THIS FEELS BETTER.

05:31.287 --> 05:36.379
[GENTLE MUSIC]

05:51.263 --> 05:52.700
-I WANNA SAIL EVERY SKY,

05:53.962 --> 05:56.225
FROM VALLEY TO BORA BORA,

05:57.052 --> 05:58.749
FROM THE KREMLIN TO KATMANDU.

05:58.880 --> 05:59.750
YOU NAME IT.

06:03.406 --> 06:04.451
COME WITH ME.

06:05.408 --> 06:06.366
-RIGHT.

06:06.496 --> 06:07.932
-I'M SERIOUS CJ.

06:09.456 --> 06:13.677
CAN YOU IMAGINE A MORE
EXCITING ADVENTURE?

06:13.808 --> 06:15.505
COME SAIL THE SKIES WITH ME.

06:16.245 --> 06:17.420
-WELL I CAN SEE WHY YOU'RE SUCH

06:17.551 --> 06:18.987
A GOOD ADVERTISING EXECUTIVE.

06:19.117 --> 06:20.423
-I'M GIVING IT ALL UP.

06:21.511 --> 06:23.687
DO THE SAME. COME WITH ME.

06:26.951 --> 06:30.433
-WE'VE GONE OUT TWICE, SIMON.
WE HARDLY KNOW EACH OTHER.

06:31.086 --> 06:33.349
-I KNOW ALL I NEED
TO KNOW ABOUT YOU CJ.

06:35.264 --> 06:37.440
PROMISE ME YOU'LL AT
LEAST THINK ABOUT IT.

06:44.099 --> 06:49.191
-FINE, BUT THE ANSWER IS
ABSOLUTELY, DEFINITELY...

06:51.019 --> 06:53.021
ALMOST NO.
-ALMOST.

06:53.543 --> 06:55.893
I DETECT A CHINK IN THAT ARMOR.

06:58.330 --> 06:59.201
-I GOTTA GET TO WORK.

07:02.987 --> 07:04.293
BYE.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.558
OH, AND THANKS FOR TODAY.
IT WAS FUN.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.081
IT WAS INTERESTING.

07:11.387 --> 07:12.432
-I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

07:18.350 --> 07:21.179
-MIMI, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT? YOUR HIP?

07:22.093 --> 07:24.661
-MY HIP IS MUCH WORSE
THAN YOUR LEGS, ROSE.

07:24.792 --> 07:27.447
-OH PLEASE, MY LEGS ARE SO NUMB

07:27.577 --> 07:29.187
I DON'T EVEN FEEL
'EM WHEN I WALK.

07:29.840 --> 07:31.538
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE COMPLAINING ABOUT

07:31.668 --> 07:34.279
BECAUSE IF I STEP WRONG, MY
HIP GOES OUT AND I FALL.

07:34.410 --> 07:35.367
WHAT DO I DO ABOUT THAT?

07:35.498 --> 07:36.978
-WELL THAT'S BECAUSE YOU...

07:37.108 --> 07:38.632
-HEY! HEY!

07:39.937 --> 07:42.505
-YOU WOULD LOVE ME TO LOOK
LIKE AN INVALID, WOULDN'T YOU?

07:42.636 --> 07:43.985
-YOU ARE SO VAIN.

07:44.115 --> 07:46.030
YOU'D RATHER FALL
AND BREAK YOUR HIP.

07:46.161 --> 07:49.860
-ROSE, IF YOU WERE AS PRETTY
AS I AM, YOU'D BE VAIN TOO.

07:51.209 --> 07:52.863
-YOU KNOW YOU'RE
DROPPING A STITCH.

07:52.994 --> 07:58.086
[TECHNO MUSIC]

09:24.694 --> 09:29.699
[SIRENS]

10:20.794 --> 10:22.099
-WHAT'D HE DO?

10:22.230 --> 10:23.623
-I THINK THAT'S
THE TOAD THAT'S BEEN

10:23.753 --> 10:25.320
SNATCHING PURSES UP
AND DOWN THE BEACH.

10:26.451 --> 10:28.410
STOP THAT.
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

10:29.106 --> 10:30.630
-WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
LEARN THAT THE SAND

10:30.760 --> 10:32.762
IS A LIFEGUARD'S DOMAIN ANYWAY?

10:32.893 --> 10:34.895
-IF I'D HAD MY HORSE,
HE'D NEVER GOTTEN TO THE SAND.

10:35.025 --> 10:37.375
-STILL WANNA PLAY
COWBOY COP HUH?

10:37.506 --> 10:39.595
-LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.
YOU PUT ME ON HORSEBACK,
AND I'LL CLEAN UP THIS AREA LIKE

10:39.726 --> 10:41.466
WYATT EARP CLEANED UP TOMBSTONE.

10:41.597 --> 10:43.338
-YEAH, WELL WHO'S GONNA
CLEAN UP AFTER THE HORSE?

10:43.468 --> 10:44.861
PEOPLE GO BAREFOOT OUT HERE.

10:44.992 --> 10:47.168
-SMALL PRICE TO PAY
MITCH, A SMALL PRICE.

10:47.298 --> 10:49.213
MOUNTED PATROL,
THAT IS THE ANSWER.

10:49.344 --> 10:51.433
HORSES DON'T RUN OUT OF GAS.

10:53.740 --> 10:56.743
I'M GONNA GET IT DONE IF
IT'S THE LAST THING I DO.

10:56.873 --> 11:02.705
[JUBILANT MUSIC]

11:14.325 --> 11:15.936
-HEY MOLLY.
-HI CJ.

11:50.318 --> 11:52.102
-HEY, THERE'S ONE.

11:55.105 --> 11:58.239
-EXCUSE ME. I'M SORRY. I
DIDN'T MEAN TO GET SAND ON YOU.

11:59.762 --> 12:01.372
WELL, GREAT DAY, HUH?

12:02.547 --> 12:04.724
-SORRY, COME ON.
-OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

12:05.376 --> 12:06.595
TAKE IT EASY.

12:18.476 --> 12:21.741
[PHONE RINGING]

12:24.352 --> 12:25.745
-TOWER 18, PARKER.

12:27.268 --> 12:30.227
SIMON, MY BOSS IS COMING.
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU.

12:31.881 --> 12:34.623
SIMON, I CAN'T TAKE
PERSONAL CALLS HERE.

12:35.885 --> 12:38.409
NO, I WILL NOT FLY
TO HAWAII WITH YOU.

12:38.540 --> 12:41.064
DON'T CALL ME ANYMORE, OKAY?

12:41.804 --> 12:43.675
I GOTTA GO. I GOTTA GO.
MY BOSS IS COMING.

12:43.806 --> 12:45.416
YOU'RE BUGGING ME.
WILL YOU STOP IT?

12:47.592 --> 12:48.463
HI!

12:50.073 --> 12:50.900
-HI.

12:52.772 --> 12:53.773
WHO'S THAT?

12:53.903 --> 12:56.906
-OH, I REPORTED A LOST CHILD,

12:57.037 --> 12:59.300
BUT THEY FOUND HIM,
SO IT'S OKAY.

12:59.430 --> 13:00.301
WHAT'S UP?

13:01.519 --> 13:02.390
-I DON'T KNOW.

13:04.000 --> 13:05.697
THINK WE'RE ABOUT TO FIND OUT.

13:05.828 --> 13:07.743
-LIFEGUARD, CAN YOU HELP US?

13:12.269 --> 13:13.662
WHAT'S WRONG?

13:13.793 --> 13:15.359
-SOMEONE STOLE MY PURSE.
IT WAS RIGHT THERE,

13:15.490 --> 13:16.534
AND THEN IT DISAPPEARED.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.581
-I DIDN'T TAKE MY
EYES OFF THE BEACH.

13:19.711 --> 13:21.017
-CALL GARNER.

13:25.761 --> 13:30.810
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

13:38.905 --> 13:40.820
WHAT THE...

14:07.368 --> 14:08.891
-WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

14:09.022 --> 14:11.938
-AH, WE JUST HAD A SERIOUS
ORDINANCE VIOLATION.

14:12.068 --> 14:14.723
-WAIT, WAIT WAIT. YOU CALLED
ME HERE ON AN
ORDINANCE VIOLATION?

14:14.854 --> 14:16.116
-NO, I CALLED YOU HERE BECAUSE

14:16.246 --> 14:18.074
THESE LADIES'
PURSES WERE STOLEN.

14:18.945 --> 14:20.598
YOU COMMITTED THE
ORDINANCE VIOLATION.

14:20.729 --> 14:22.426
-WHAT?

14:22.557 --> 14:23.993
-WHAT THE HELL IS THIS THING
DOING ON THE BEACH ANYWAY?

14:24.124 --> 14:25.647
PEOPLE COULD BE
TRAMPLED OUT THERE.

14:25.777 --> 14:29.042
-OH NEVER, MY DAD OWNED
A HORSE RANCH IN GEORGIA.

14:29.172 --> 14:31.783
I LEARNED TO RIDE HORSES
BEFORE I LEARNED TO WALK.

14:31.914 --> 14:34.090
YOU AND YOUR LIFEGUARD
TRUCKS ARE FAR MORE DANGEROUS

14:34.221 --> 14:35.918
THAN ME AND KOJAK HERE.

14:36.049 --> 14:38.138
NOW YOU LADIES TELL ME
EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED.

14:38.268 --> 14:41.358
[THUMPING]

14:41.489 --> 14:43.143
-OH, UCK.

14:44.884 --> 14:47.451
UH, YOUR HORSE
DROPPED SOMETHING.

14:52.065 --> 14:53.501
KOJAK HUH?

14:55.938 --> 14:57.679
TELLY SAVALAS NEVER DID THAT.

15:06.253 --> 15:08.646
-NOW YOU BEHAVE YOURSELF.
YOU UNDERSTAND?

15:08.777 --> 15:10.561
-SEEMS LIKE THE PURSE
SNATCHER YOU RAN DOWN

15:10.692 --> 15:12.476
THIS MORNING WASN'T
THE ONE WE WERE AFTER.

15:12.607 --> 15:14.652
-I RAN DOWN. YOU WERE
THE ONE WHO WAS AFTER HIM.

15:16.393 --> 15:18.743
-STOP. GO!

15:32.105 --> 15:33.584
-LOOK LADIES, CAN
YOU DESCRIBE THE MEN

15:33.715 --> 15:35.325
WHO DROPPED THEIR
PROPERTY NEAR YOUR TOWELS?

15:35.978 --> 15:37.371
-I'LL BE BACK.

15:38.154 --> 15:43.116
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:59.523 --> 16:03.179
-AH LOOK, I GOTTA BACK CJ UP.
TIE UP KOJAK WILL YA?

16:08.402 --> 16:11.013
[SCREAMING]

16:18.412 --> 16:19.630
-HANG ON.

16:34.428 --> 16:35.690
-SALLY, YOU ALL RIGHT?

16:35.820 --> 16:36.734
-I'M OKAY.

16:42.305 --> 16:43.915
-GOOD ANTICIPATION OUT THERE.

16:44.046 --> 16:45.134
-THANKS.

16:45.265 --> 16:46.570
-AMAZING ISN'T IT?

16:47.267 --> 16:48.746
-WHAT?

16:48.877 --> 16:50.531
-HOW A HIGHLY TRAINED
PROFESSIONAL CAN SPOT

16:50.661 --> 16:52.837
A POTENTIAL PROBLEM BEFORE
IT HAPPENS TO SOMEONE ELSE,

16:52.968 --> 16:54.317
BUT NOT TO YOURSELF.

16:55.231 --> 16:56.276
-WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

16:56.406 --> 16:58.408
-SIMON, THE HOT
AIR BALLOON MAN.

16:58.539 --> 17:00.976
WITH EMPHASIS ON HOT AIR.

17:01.107 --> 17:04.501
-I'M AWARE OF THE PROBLEM.
BELIEVE ME.

17:05.328 --> 17:06.938
I ALREADY TOLD SIMON
TO LEAVE ME ALONE.

17:07.069 --> 17:07.896
HE GOT THE MESSAGE.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.202
-NO HE DIDN'T.

17:09.332 --> 17:11.073
-YES HE DID.
-NO HE DIDN'T.

17:11.204 --> 17:12.988
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
HE'S GIVING YOU THE MESSAGE,

17:13.118 --> 17:16.818
AND IT'S ABOUT 40
FEET LONG I'D SAY.

17:25.392 --> 17:27.915
[GENTLE MUSIC]

17:44.454 --> 17:46.108
-TOUGH WORKOUT, HUH?

17:49.024 --> 17:50.547
-I NEEDED IT, WHAT'S UP?

17:51.200 --> 17:51.983
-NOTHING.

17:52.114 --> 17:53.333
-NOTHING?

17:53.985 --> 17:55.030
-NOTHING MUCH.

17:55.596 --> 17:56.684
-YEAH RIGHT.

17:56.814 --> 17:57.859
-MATT!

18:02.342 --> 18:03.691
WHAT?

18:03.821 --> 18:05.475
-I SAW YOUR HAPPY
REUNION WITH SLADE.

18:08.174 --> 18:11.046
-COME ON, MATT.
I WAS TOTALLY STUNNED.

18:11.177 --> 18:13.179
I MEAN, I HAVEN'T TALKED
TO THE GUY IN MONTHS,

18:13.309 --> 18:15.050
AND THEN ALL OF A
SUDDEN, THERE HE WAS.

18:15.181 --> 18:16.704
-DID YOU TELL HIM ABOUT US?

18:18.009 --> 18:18.793
-NO, I--

18:18.923 --> 18:20.055
-WHY NOT?

18:20.664 --> 18:22.666
-WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO SAY?

18:22.797 --> 18:25.887
OH IT'S GREAT TO SEE YOU AFTER
FOUR MONTHS, AND BY THE WAY,

18:26.017 --> 18:28.194
WHILE YOU WERE GONE YOUR BEST
FRIEND AND I FELL IN LOVE?

18:28.324 --> 18:29.586
-WELL THAT'S WHAT
HAPPENED ISN'T IT?

18:30.326 --> 18:31.545
-WELL IF YOU THINK IT'S SO EASY

18:31.675 --> 18:32.633
THEN WHY DON'T YOU TELL HIM?

18:33.242 --> 18:34.635
-WELL, ONE OF US SHOULD
BEFORE HE FINDS OUT

18:34.765 --> 18:36.245
FROM SOMEBODY ELSE.

18:36.376 --> 18:39.596
THAT'S IF THERE'S ANYTHING
TO TELL, IS THERE?

18:40.467 --> 18:42.208
-YES MATT, THERE IS.

18:44.384 --> 18:46.212
YOU JUST GOTTA GIVE
ME A LITTLE TIME

18:46.342 --> 18:48.431
TO FIGURE OUT WHAT
I'M GONNA SAY, OKAY?

19:00.617 --> 19:04.491
-SLADE! HEY BRO. I HEAR
YOU WENT OFF OVERSEAS, MAN.

19:04.621 --> 19:06.057
-I HANG IN THERE.
HOW'S IT GOING ETHAN?

19:06.188 --> 19:07.624
-NO COMPLAINTS BRO.

19:07.755 --> 19:09.626
-ALL RIGHT.
-COME ON, LET'S GO FOR A SURF.

19:09.757 --> 19:12.151
-AH, I CAN'T, I GOTTA
REGISTER FOR CLASS.

19:12.281 --> 19:14.414
-BACK IN CLASS? ALL RIGHT.

19:14.544 --> 19:16.720
OH HEY MAN LISTEN,
SATURDAY NIGHT,

19:16.851 --> 19:19.114
HAVING A PARTY AT MY HOUSE.
BE THERE OKAY?

19:19.245 --> 19:21.072
-ALL RIGHT.
I'LL CHECK WITH SUMMER.

19:21.943 --> 19:23.771
-I WOULDN'T WASTE
TIME ON THAT, MAN.

19:23.901 --> 19:25.076
-WHY NOT?

19:25.207 --> 19:27.035
-NOTHING MAN, IT'S--

19:28.384 --> 19:29.907
-HEY, ANSWER THE QUESTION.

19:31.213 --> 19:32.780
-REALLY, IT'S NOTHING BRO.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.825
-WHY SHOULDN'T I WASTE
MY TIME WITH SUMMER?

19:38.829 --> 19:41.136
-SLADE, WHILE YOU WERE GONE,

19:41.267 --> 19:43.660
SUMMER, SHE AND MATT,
THEY'VE BEEN GOING OUT.

20:07.118 --> 20:11.210
-[GASPS] JIMMY, YOU SCARED ME.

20:11.819 --> 20:13.821
-YEAH, WELL WHAT I
JUST HEARD SCARED ME.

20:15.388 --> 20:17.346
-YEAH? WHAT DID YOU HEAR?

20:17.912 --> 20:19.609
-A LITTLE STORY
ABOUT YOU AND MATT.

20:23.004 --> 20:23.961
SO IS IT TRUE?

20:26.573 --> 20:30.359
-JIMMY, WE NEED TO TALK,
ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS.

20:31.360 --> 20:33.362
BUT I CAN'T RIGHT NOW,
BECAUSE I'M ON DUTY.

20:33.493 --> 20:34.972
SO CAN IT WAIT?

20:35.103 --> 20:36.191
-SUMMER, I THOUGHT WE
HAD SOMETHING SPECIAL.

20:37.888 --> 20:40.108
-WE DID, YOU KNOW,
AND THEN YOU LEFT.

20:41.022 --> 20:44.155
I GOT EXACTLY ONE PHONE CALL
AND TWO POSTCARDS.

20:44.286 --> 20:46.027
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO?

20:46.157 --> 20:47.594
-WAIT, LIKE I DID.

20:47.724 --> 20:49.073
-WAIT?

20:49.204 --> 20:50.901
IS THAT WHAT YOU DID? WAIT?

20:51.032 --> 20:52.033
-YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I DID.

20:53.948 --> 20:55.515
-YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T
KNOW HOW MANY TIMES

20:55.645 --> 20:58.213
PEOPLE CAME UP TO ME WITH
THESE SURFING MAGAZINES

20:58.344 --> 21:00.433
WITH PICTURES OF YOU
WINNING THESE TOURNAMENTS

21:00.563 --> 21:02.913
SURROUNDED BY GIRLS IN
LITTLE THONG BIKINIS.

21:03.914 --> 21:05.481
-SURE I HAD OPPORTUNITIES,

21:05.612 --> 21:07.266
BUT I DIDN'T CHEAT
ON YOU, NOT ONCE.

21:12.358 --> 21:14.534
-YOU KNOW, MATT AND I,
WE DIDN'T PLAN THIS

21:14.664 --> 21:17.711
BEHIND YOUR BACK.
IT JUST KINDA HAPPENED.

21:18.929 --> 21:20.191
I MEAN, MAYBE IT
WOULDN'T OF IF YOU--

21:20.322 --> 21:22.977
-YOU'RE RIGHT.
I SHOULD'VE WRITTEN.

21:23.107 --> 21:25.588
I SHOULD'VE CALLED MORE.
I'M SORRY.

21:25.719 --> 21:29.331
-SO AM I.
-SO WHAT NOW?

21:31.290 --> 21:32.595
-I DON'T KNOW.

21:39.385 --> 21:40.429
ARE YOU LOST?

21:40.560 --> 21:41.909
COME ON. LET'S FIND YOUR MOM.

21:57.577 --> 22:03.365
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

23:33.324 --> 23:38.852
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

24:21.285 --> 24:27.161
[ROCK MUSIC]

25:17.864 --> 25:19.300
-YOU JUMPED ON MY WAVE, MAN.

25:20.736 --> 25:23.217
-YOU DROPPED IN ON SOMETHING
THAT MEANT A HELL OF A LOT
MORE TO ME THAN A WAVE.

25:23.347 --> 25:25.480
-ONLY AFTER YOU GAVE UP ON IT.

25:27.177 --> 25:28.309
-HEY, SUMMER AND I
WERE STILL GOING OUT.

25:28.439 --> 25:30.006
YOU DON'T DO THAT TO A FRIEND.

25:30.137 --> 25:31.660
-SLADE, WHATEVER HAPPENED
BETWEEN SUMMER AND ME

25:31.791 --> 25:33.096
DOESN'T HAVE TO
RUIN OUR FRIENDSHIP.

25:33.227 --> 25:34.968
COME ON, MAN.
YOU MUST HAVE GONE OUT

25:35.098 --> 25:36.360
WITH A BUNCH OF GIRLS WHILE
YOU WERE SURFING THE GLOBE.

25:36.491 --> 25:38.667
-NO. I WAS THERE
TO SURF. THAT'S ALL.

25:38.798 --> 25:40.190
I'D NEVER DO WHAT YOU DID.

25:40.321 --> 25:41.801
-WELL I WOULD'VE NEVER
DONE WHAT YOU DID.

25:41.931 --> 25:43.367
-ME?
-YEAH, YOU.

25:43.498 --> 25:45.587
I WOULD'VE NEVER
DUMPED SUMMER FOR THIS.

25:47.763 --> 25:51.854
[GRUNTING]

25:53.682 --> 25:54.770
COME ON!

26:12.701 --> 26:13.659
ARE YOU OKAY?

26:29.936 --> 26:30.850
YOU OKAY SLADE?

26:30.980 --> 26:32.591
-YEAH.

26:32.721 --> 26:34.680
-I'M SORRY, MAN. THE WAVE
JUST KNOCKED ME OVER.

26:36.377 --> 26:37.639
-IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

26:38.509 --> 26:40.468
I STARTED IT, AND I
GOT WHAT I DESERVED.

26:40.599 --> 26:42.470
-YOU DIDN'T DESERVE WHAT I DID.

26:44.690 --> 26:45.821
LOOK, I'LL BACK OFF.

26:47.170 --> 26:48.607
-NO, SUMMER CHOSE YOU.

26:49.259 --> 26:50.217
YOU'RE THE ONE SHE WANTS.

26:50.347 --> 26:51.218
-NO.

26:52.393 --> 26:54.743
WE WORK TOGETHER.
IT WILL COMPLICATE THINGS.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.703
WE'RE BETTER OFF BEING FRIENDS.

26:59.182 --> 27:01.054
YOU AND SUMMER SHOULD
GET BACK TOGETHER.

27:01.184 --> 27:03.099
-THEN WHAT HAPPENS
NEXT TIME I GO AWAY?

27:06.886 --> 27:08.278
I THINK SUMMER SHOULD DECIDE.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.195
-I DON'T THINK SHE CAN
HANDLE IT RIGHT NOW.

27:12.326 --> 27:15.677
SHE'S-- I DON'T KNOW. SHE'S
HAVING A BAD TIME WITH THIS.

27:15.808 --> 27:17.461
I THINK WE SHOULD
DECIDE BETWEEN US.

27:18.680 --> 27:19.594
-HOW?

27:21.204 --> 27:22.249
-SURFING?

27:22.379 --> 27:23.380
-GET REAL.

27:24.294 --> 27:25.252
-DIRT BIKE RACING.

27:25.382 --> 27:27.297
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

27:27.994 --> 27:28.821
-THEN WHAT?

27:30.910 --> 27:35.349
[GENTLE MUSIC]

27:37.351 --> 27:40.659
-CJ, PICK UP YOUR BINOCULARS.

27:42.573 --> 27:43.836
LOOK OUT TOWARDS THE HORIZON.

27:48.449 --> 27:50.581
-ALL RIGHT SIMON. I SEE YOU.

27:52.105 --> 27:53.106
-YOU SEE WHO'S WITH ME?

27:54.107 --> 27:55.064
-NO.

27:55.195 --> 27:56.936
-THAT'S BECAUSE I'M ALONE.

27:57.980 --> 27:59.765
I NEED YOU UP HERE CJ.

27:59.895 --> 28:01.767
IT'S THE LAST TIME
I'M GONNA ASK.

28:01.897 --> 28:03.072
SAY YES.

28:03.203 --> 28:04.073
-NO.

28:04.204 --> 28:04.987
-YOU SURE?

28:05.118 --> 28:06.685
-YES.

28:06.815 --> 28:09.426
-GREAT, YOU'LL NEVER
REGRET CHANGING YOUR MIND.

28:09.557 --> 28:12.299
-I DIDN'T CHANGE MY MIND, SIMON.
THE ANSWER'S STILL NO.

28:12.429 --> 28:13.474
-YOU SURE?

28:15.128 --> 28:16.390
-YEAH, I'M SURE.

28:17.043 --> 28:18.218
-ARE YOU WATCHING?

28:19.523 --> 28:20.394
CJ?

28:21.569 --> 28:22.701
-I'M WATCHING.

28:24.180 --> 28:26.487
-I CAN'T BEAR TO BE
UP HERE WITHOUT YOU.

28:35.670 --> 28:40.849
[OMINOUS MUSIC]
-NO!

28:47.987 --> 28:49.075
-WHOA!

28:50.206 --> 28:52.948
[LAUGHING]

28:57.213 --> 28:58.867
-OH MY GOD.

29:04.394 --> 29:07.528
OH, THIS IS GREAT.

29:07.658 --> 29:09.008
YOU'VE GOTTA TRY IT.

29:09.791 --> 29:12.707
-OH I HOPE YOUR BALLOON POPS.

29:13.490 --> 29:16.929
[LAUGHING]

29:17.059 --> 29:18.234
-I GOTTA DO THAT.

29:19.235 --> 29:20.584
-CLOSEST TO THE WATER.

29:21.716 --> 29:23.326
-OKAY, LOSER BACKS OFF.

29:24.414 --> 29:25.285
-YOU GOT IT.

29:27.940 --> 29:30.594
-OKAY, YOU GOTTA GET YOUR
HANDS WET, AND NOT YOUR TRUNKS.

29:32.031 --> 29:34.555
-WINNER GOES WITH SUMMER,
AND LOSER GOES AWAY.

29:34.685 --> 29:36.122
-OKAY.

29:38.037 --> 29:39.125
-LET'S DO IT.

29:55.489 --> 29:56.838
-CJ, CAN YOU WATCH MY WATER?

29:56.969 --> 29:58.405
I'VE GOTTA RUN TO THE BATHROOM.

29:58.535 --> 30:00.233
-SUMMER, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

30:00.363 --> 30:01.930
-YEAH I'M FINE.

30:04.106 --> 30:05.238
-I DON'T THINK SO.

30:05.368 --> 30:06.805
-NO REALLY, I--

30:06.935 --> 30:08.719
-SUMMER, I'VE BEEN WATCHING
YOU LATELY.

30:08.850 --> 30:11.157
THE WAY YOU'VE BEEN
EATING AND THEN
RUNNING TO THE BATHROOM.

30:12.419 --> 30:14.725
-WELL I'VE JUST HAD THIS
REALLY NERVOUS STOMACH.

30:19.382 --> 30:21.254
-DID I EVER TELL YOU
THAT IN HIGH SCHOOL

30:21.384 --> 30:23.125
I HAD A EATING DISORDER?

30:24.213 --> 30:26.650
BULIMIA.
-NO.

30:28.130 --> 30:30.611
-WELL IT'S NOT SOMETHING
I ENJOY TALKING ABOUT,

30:31.830 --> 30:34.441
BUT TALKING ABOUT IT IS
WHAT MADE ME GET BETTER.

30:35.921 --> 30:40.621
IT WASN'T EASY, BUT I HAD TO
COME TO A POINT WHERE I COULD

30:40.751 --> 30:44.190
ADMIT IT TO MYSELF BEFORE I
COULD ADMIT IT TO ANYBODY ELSE.

30:45.974 --> 30:49.325
-CJ, I DON'T HAVE BULIMIA.

30:50.283 --> 30:51.937
-THAT'S WHAT I KEPT SAYING.

30:52.938 --> 30:57.943
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

31:06.168 --> 31:10.781
-HI. I'M MATT. I'M A LIFEGUARD.
I'M A FRIEND OF CJ'S.

31:10.912 --> 31:12.131
CAN WE COME UP?

31:12.261 --> 31:13.959
-SURE, COME ON.

31:20.182 --> 31:23.055
-IT'S JUST THAT SOMETIMES
I FEEL SO EMPTY INSIDE

31:23.185 --> 31:27.059
THAT I HAVE TO EAT, AND
THEN I EAT SO MUCH FOOD

31:27.189 --> 31:29.888
AND I'M SO STUFFED THAT
I CAN'T EVEN STAND IT.

31:30.758 --> 31:32.978
-WELL IT'S NOT ABOUT
THE FOOD YOU EAT.

31:33.108 --> 31:36.329
-I KNOW. IT'S THIS THING
WITH MATT AND SLADE.

31:36.459 --> 31:37.852
-IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

31:37.983 --> 31:42.596
-YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE ONE
MINUTE I WANT THEM BOTH,

31:42.726 --> 31:44.903
AND THEN THE NEXT
MINUTE I DON'T WANT

31:45.033 --> 31:46.165
TO BE WITH EITHER ONE OF 'EM.

31:48.123 --> 31:50.909
MY MOM TELLS ME THAT
I SHOULD CHOOSE ONE,

31:51.648 --> 31:52.867
WHICH IS IMPOSSIBLE.

31:54.129 --> 31:56.566
I MEAN MATT IS SO WONDERFUL,

31:58.394 --> 31:59.961
BUT JIMMY, HE WAS MY FIRST LOVE.

32:00.092 --> 32:01.702
-SUMMER, YOU HAVE
TO STOP PUTTING

32:01.832 --> 32:03.051
SO MUCH PRESSURE ON YOURSELF.

32:03.182 --> 32:05.227
-I KNOW.

32:07.055 --> 32:09.014
SOMETIMES I WISH THAT
THEY WOULD JUST DECIDE IT

32:09.144 --> 32:11.973
AMONG THEMSELVES, AND
THEN JUST LET ME KNOW.

32:16.673 --> 32:19.328
-ALL RIGHT, I'M ONLY
LETTING YOU GUYS DO THIS

32:19.459 --> 32:21.330
BECAUSE IT'S ABOUT
THE LOVE OF A WOMAN.

32:21.461 --> 32:23.202
AND THAT'S WORTH
TAKING A RISK FOR.

32:27.206 --> 32:29.773
-OH WHAT IS THIS GUY DOING NOW?

32:36.389 --> 32:38.608
-MATT AND SLADE ARE
UP THERE WITH HIM.

32:38.739 --> 32:41.742
-ALL RIGHT, WHICH ONE OF
YOU WANTS TO GO FIRST?

32:41.872 --> 32:43.918
-AT THE SAME TIME.
-WANNA GO AT THE SAME TIME.

32:45.485 --> 32:46.921
-YOU KNOW, JUMPING
THIS CLOSE TO THE WATER

32:47.052 --> 32:48.967
IS RISKY ENOUGH AS IT IS.

32:52.361 --> 32:53.928
-THEN I'LL GO FIRST.

32:54.798 --> 32:56.496
-ALL RIGHT.
-FINE.

33:02.632 --> 33:04.765
-CJ, SLADE'S JUMPING.

33:14.775 --> 33:16.211
-SLADE!

33:19.780 --> 33:20.694
SLADE!

33:30.312 --> 33:33.054
-PARKER, REQUESTING
IMMEDIATE BACKUP. TOWER 18.

33:33.663 --> 33:39.104
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

33:39.234 --> 33:40.583
-OH MY GOD!

33:41.758 --> 33:43.021
SHORTEN MY CORD.

33:43.151 --> 33:43.934
-HUH?

33:44.065 --> 33:45.632
-SHORTEN MY CORD!

33:45.762 --> 33:50.115
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:26.063 --> 34:27.804
-HURRY! FASTER!

34:42.123 --> 34:43.646
-SUMMER! HELP!

34:49.304 --> 34:50.784
-PUT THIS UNDER HIM.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.105
COME ON.

35:08.671 --> 35:11.935
[COUGHING]

35:21.728 --> 35:23.251
[WHINNYING]

35:27.212 --> 35:28.996
-ONE OF THE BEST
COWBOYS OF ALL TIME

35:29.127 --> 35:32.086
WAS AN AFRICAN
AMERICAN, BILL PICKETT.

35:32.217 --> 35:35.829
HE WAS SO GOOD, TOM
MIX AND WILL ROGERS

35:35.959 --> 35:38.266
WERE BOTH HIS ASSISTANTS
AT ONE TIME OR ANOTHER.

35:39.354 --> 35:42.052
HE INVENTED BULLDOGGING
IN HIS RODEO EVENT.

35:43.010 --> 35:46.622
CHECK THIS OUT.
PICKETT WAS ACTUALLY SEEN BITING

35:46.753 --> 35:49.364
INTO A STEER'S LIP AND LETTING
GO WITH BOTH HIS HANDS.

35:49.495 --> 35:51.497
DRUG HIM TO THE
GROUND WITH HIS TEETH.

35:52.802 --> 35:57.067
BOY, BILL PICKETT. YEAH, THAT
WAS MY IDOL WHEN I WAS A KID.

35:58.547 --> 35:59.896
-WELL LET'S JUST
HOPE WE GET OUR HANDS

36:00.027 --> 36:01.376
ON THOSE PURSE SNATCHERS
BEFORE YOU END UP

36:01.507 --> 36:03.073
SINKING YOUR TEETH INTO 'EM.

36:05.206 --> 36:08.644
HOW'D YOU GET YOUR CAPTAIN TO
PUT YOU ON HORSEBACK ANYWAY?

36:08.775 --> 36:11.299
-WELL, I JUST LAID OUT THE PROS
AND CONS OF A MOUNTED PATROL

36:11.430 --> 36:13.649
ON THE BEACH, AND HE SAID
LET'S GIVE IT A TRY.

36:13.780 --> 36:15.129
-FOR HOW LONG?

36:15.260 --> 36:17.044
-IF IT WORKS, PERMANENTLY.

36:17.175 --> 36:18.567
RIGHT KOJAK?

36:18.698 --> 36:20.308
-KOJAK, WHA-- WHAT'S
WITH THE NAME KOJAK

36:20.439 --> 36:22.658
FOR A HORSE ANYWAY,
KOJAK WAS BALD.

36:37.325 --> 36:38.674
-NEED I SAY MORE?

36:41.677 --> 36:43.897
-COME ON. LET'S GO ROUND UP
SOME BAD GUYS.

37:04.700 --> 37:05.962
SPOT ANYTHING YET?

37:07.486 --> 37:09.052
-NOTHING HAPPENING.

37:44.131 --> 37:45.828
-SORRY LADIES.

37:45.959 --> 37:47.352
I'M SO CLUMSY.

37:47.482 --> 37:49.789
-COME ON, YOU FOOL.

37:52.139 --> 37:54.054
-IT'S GOING DOWN. SOUTH OF 20.

37:59.015 --> 38:01.670
[WHINNYING]

38:18.121 --> 38:18.905
[HORSE WHINNYING]

38:19.035 --> 38:23.475
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

38:35.269 --> 38:39.534
[GRUNTING]

39:08.955 --> 39:11.523
-OKAY, I GOT HIM, JAWS.
I GOT HIM. I GOT HIM.

39:11.653 --> 39:13.307
-COME ON.

39:13.438 --> 39:15.788
-YOU KNOW, SOMEDAY THEY'RE
GONNA BE TALKING ABOUT YOU

39:15.918 --> 39:17.311
IN THE SAME BREATH
AS BILL PICKETT.

39:17.442 --> 39:20.488
-YEAH, ME AND BILL PICKETT.
I LIKE THAT.

39:21.054 --> 39:23.883
-OR MAYBE HANNIBAL LECTER,
YOU KNOW? ONE OR THE OTHER.

39:24.013 --> 39:24.840
OR MAYBE BRUCE.

39:24.971 --> 39:25.972
-BRUCE WHO?

39:26.102 --> 39:27.800
-YOU KNOW, THE SHARK FROM JAWS.

39:27.930 --> 39:28.844
OR MAYBE CUJO.

39:28.975 --> 39:30.716
-SHUT UP.

39:30.846 --> 39:34.154
-OR MAYBE BENJI, OR DID YOU
SEE THAT MOVIE FREE WILLY?

39:37.636 --> 39:38.941
-HEY, FRIEND.

39:40.769 --> 39:42.423
-YOU KNOW MAYBE IF YOUR PARENT
HAD DONE THAT TO YOU

39:42.554 --> 39:44.294
WHEN YOU WERE YOUNG,
YOU WOULDN'T BE SO OBNOXIOUS.

39:44.425 --> 39:46.035
I DON'T WANT TO BE
YOUR FRIEND SIMON.

39:46.166 --> 39:47.820
I DON'T WANT TO EVER SEE
YOU OR HEAR FROM YOU AGAIN.

39:47.950 --> 39:49.604
YOU COULD'VE GOTTEN
THOSE GUYS KILLED.

39:59.658 --> 40:01.703
-WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU TWO DOING?

40:01.834 --> 40:04.053
-LOOK, SUMMER, WE KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GOING
THROUGH IS DIFFICULT.

40:04.184 --> 40:06.012
-YEAH, WE DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO HAVE TO MAKE A CHOICE.

40:06.142 --> 40:07.840
-YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO BOTHER.

40:07.970 --> 40:09.319
-WHY?

40:09.450 --> 40:11.496
-BECAUSE I'VE ALREADY
MADE MY CHOICE.

40:14.020 --> 40:15.935
I WANT YOU BOTH AS FRIENDS.

40:16.065 --> 40:19.852
WE ALL CARE TOO MUCH ABOUT
EACH OTHER TO LET THIS RUIN IT.

40:21.897 --> 40:23.290
OKAY?

40:24.813 --> 40:25.988
-OKAY.

40:27.468 --> 40:30.297
-I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU
GUYS ACTUALLY JUMPED
OUT OF A BALLOON.

40:30.428 --> 40:31.733
-ME NEITHER.

40:37.478 --> 40:38.871
-BEAUTIFUL.
-WHAT'S THAT?

40:39.001 --> 40:41.526
-THAT IS A RAIL
FOR GARNER'S HORSE.

40:41.656 --> 40:42.744
WHAT'S THAT?

40:42.875 --> 40:44.224
-OH, I GOT THESE FOR KOJAK.

40:44.354 --> 40:45.704
THEY'RE BETTER FOR HIM
THAN TOOTSIE ROLL POPS.

40:45.834 --> 40:48.315
-DON'T GET THOSE
TOO CLOSE TO GARNER.

40:50.622 --> 40:51.623
LOOKS GOOD HUH?

40:53.407 --> 40:54.887
-HEY.
-OH NO.

40:55.017 --> 40:56.628
-OH NO, WHAT'S THIS?

40:56.758 --> 40:58.499
-WHERE'S KOJAK?

40:58.630 --> 41:01.894
-KOJAK IS BACK IN THE BARN,
AND I'M BACK RIDING THIS THING.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.549
-WHAT HAPPENED?

41:04.679 --> 41:07.160
-WELL, I WROTE UP MY REPORT,
AND THE BOTTOM LINE IS

41:07.290 --> 41:09.945
MY CAPTAIN DECIDED THAT
I DIDN'T DEMONSTRATE

41:10.076 --> 41:12.339
CONTEMPORARY POLICE DECORUM.

41:13.645 --> 41:15.298
-WHAT HAPPENED TO BILL PICKETT?

41:16.038 --> 41:17.562
-I TOLD HIM ABOUT BILL PICKETT.

41:17.692 --> 41:19.477
-WHAT ABOUT CLEANING UP
THE BEACH LIKE WYATT EARP?

41:20.652 --> 41:22.044
-HE SAID IF
I WANTED TO BE A COWBOY

41:22.175 --> 41:23.959
I SHOULD JOIN THE RODEO.

41:24.090 --> 41:25.308
-WELL, WHAT'D YOU TELL HIM?

41:25.439 --> 41:27.789
-NOTHING, I JUST BEGGED.

41:27.920 --> 41:30.270
[LAUGHTER]

41:32.968 --> 41:34.927
[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
